Citation.sAbstract: The speed of sound in the temperature (303.15 to 373.15) Kand pressure range (0.1 to 100) MPa was measured for the liquid 3-pentanol, 3-methyl 3-pentanol, and 3-ethyl-3-pentanol. These results combined with the densities and isobaric heat capacity at atmospheric pressure obtained from the literature were used to calculate the density, and the isentropic and isothermal compressibilities in the same range of pressure and in the temperature interval (303.15 to 368.15) K by means of a predictor-corrector algorithm.
Citation.sTitle: Study of the volumetric properties of weakly associated alcohols by means of high-pressure speed of sound measurements
